      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:3:31:1",
      "text": [
        " سَأَلْتُ أَبَا عَبْدِ اللَّهِ ( عليه السلام ) عَنْ رَجُلٍ شَرِبَ حُسْوَةَ خَمْرٍ قَالَ يُجْلَدُ ثَمَانِينَ جَلْدَةً قَلِيلُهَا وَ كَثِيرُهَا حَرَامٌ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father and Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad, altogether, from Ibn Mahboub, from Is’haq Bin Ammar who said, ",
          "‘I asked Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> about a man who drank a sip of wine. He<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘He would be whipped eighty lashes. A little of it or more of it, is Prohibited’."
        ]
      }
